The paper deals with applying neural style transfer to stereoscopic images and videos, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as disparity estimation and occlusion mask estimation. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also addresses the issue of 3D fatigue, which is related to graphics (GR) and multimedia (MM). The proposed method involves training a neural network, which falls under artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG).
